################################################################################
# MVP 2 — AUTHENTICATION SYSTEM
# AI-Based Recruitment & Skill-Matching Platform
# Goal: Implement login/signup with role-based access (User vs Recruiter)
################################################################################

## PHASE 1: Database Schema — Users (Mongoose)
[ ] Create `User` Mongoose schema/model (/models/User.js) with fields:
    [ ] _id (ObjectId, auto-generated)
    [ ] email (unique, required, lowercase)
    [ ] passwordHash (required, select: false)
    [ ] role (String enum: 'user' | 'recruiter', required)
    [ ] fullName (required)
    [ ] phone (optional)
    [ ] isVerified (Boolean, default false)
    [ ] createdAt, updatedAt (auto via timestamps: true)
[ ] Seed test accounts in /config/seed.js:
    [ ] test-user@example.com / TestUser123 (role: user)
    [ ] test-recruiter@example.com / TestRecruiter123 (role: recruiter)

## PHASE 2: Backend — Auth API Endpoints
[ ] POST /api/auth/signup
    [ ] Validate: email format, password strength (min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number)
    [ ] Validate: role must be 'user' or 'recruiter'
    [ ] Check for duplicate email → return 409 if exists
    [ ] Hash password with bcrypt (saltRounds: 12)
    [ ] Create user record
    [ ] Generate JWT access token (expires: 15min) + refresh token (expires: 7d)
    [ ] Return: { user: {...}, accessToken, refreshToken }
[ ] POST /api/auth/login
    [ ] Validate email + password presence
    [ ] Find user by email → return 404 if not found
    [ ] Compare password with bcrypt
    [ ] Generate JWT access token + refresh token
    [ ] Return: { user: {id, email, role, full_name}, accessToken, refreshToken }
[ ] POST /api/auth/logout
    [ ] Invalidate refresh token (delete from DB or blacklist)
    [ ] Return 200 OK
[ ] POST /api/auth/refresh
    [ ] Validate refresh token
    [ ] Generate new access token
    [ ] Return: { accessToken }
[ ] GET /api/auth/me
    [ ] Protected route (verify JWT middleware)
    [ ] Return current user info
[ ] Implement JWT middleware (authMiddleware):
    [ ] Extract Bearer token from Authorization header
    [ ] Verify token signature and expiry
    [ ] Attach user to request object (req.user)
    [ ] Return 401 if token invalid/expired
[ ] Implement role-based middleware:
    [ ] requireUser → only role: 'user' allowed
    [ ] requireRecruiter → only role: 'recruiter' allowed

## PHASE 3: Frontend — Signup Page
[ ] Create SignupPage component at /signup
[ ] Implement role selection UI:
    [ ] Two toggle/radio cards: "I'm a Job Seeker" | "I'm a Recruiter"
    [ ] Visual distinction (icon + label for each role)
[ ] Build signup form with fields:
    [ ] Full Name (required)
    [ ] Email Address (required)
    [ ] Password (required, show/hide toggle)
    [ ] Confirm Password (required)
    [ ] Role (hidden field, determined by toggle above)
[ ] Add form validation with react-hook-form + zod:
    [ ] Email format
    [ ] Password: min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 number
    [ ] Confirm password must match
[ ] On submit:
    [ ] Call POST /api/auth/signup
    [ ] Show loading spinner on button
    [ ] On success: store tokens, redirect based on role:
        [ ] role: 'user' → /dashboard
        [ ] role: 'recruiter' → /recruiter
    [ ] On error: show inline error message
[ ] Add link: "Already have an account? Log in"

## PHASE 4: Frontend — Login Page
[ ] Create LoginPage component at /login
[ ] Implement role selection UI (same as signup — Job Seeker / Recruiter)
[ ] Build login form with fields:
    [ ] Email Address (required)
    [ ] Password (required, show/hide toggle)
[ ] Add form validation:
    [ ] Email format required
    [ ] Password required
[ ] On submit:
    [ ] Call POST /api/auth/login
    [ ] Show loading spinner
    [ ] On success: store tokens, redirect based on role
    [ ] On error: show "Invalid email or password" message
[ ] Add link: "Don't have an account? Sign up"
[ ] Add "Forgot Password?" link (placeholder for future MVP)

## PHASE 5: Frontend — Auth State Management
[ ] Create auth store (zustand / redux slice):
    [ ] State: user, accessToken, refreshToken, isAuthenticated, isLoading
    [ ] Actions: login, logout, refreshToken, setUser
[ ] Persist auth state to localStorage (accessToken, refreshToken, user)
[ ] Implement axios interceptor:
    [ ] Attach Authorization: Bearer <token> to all requests
    [ ] On 401 response: attempt token refresh automatically
    [ ] On refresh failure: logout user and redirect to /login
[ ] Create useAuth() custom hook:
    [ ] Exposes: user, isAuthenticated, role, login, logout

## PHASE 6: Frontend — Route Guards
[ ] Create ProtectedRoute component:
    [ ] If not authenticated → redirect to /login
    [ ] If wrong role → redirect to appropriate dashboard
[ ] Wrap /dashboard with ProtectedRoute (role: user)
[ ] Wrap /recruiter with ProtectedRoute (role: recruiter)
[ ] Show loading spinner while auth state is being determined on page load

## PHASE 7: Security Hardening
[ ] Store refresh tokens in httpOnly cookies (not localStorage) in production
[ ] Implement rate limiting on auth endpoints (max 10 requests/15min per IP)
[ ] Add CSRF protection for cookie-based auth
[ ] Sanitize all inputs before DB operations
[ ] Log failed login attempts

## DELIVERABLES / ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
[ ] A user can sign up as "Job Seeker" and be redirected to User Dashboard
[ ] A user can sign up as "Recruiter" and be redirected to Recruiter Dashboard
[ ] Login works with correct credentials; shows error on wrong credentials
[ ] JWT is sent with every API request automatically
[ ] Protected routes redirect unauthenticated users to /login
[ ] Tokens refresh automatically when access token expires
[ ] Logout clears all auth state and redirects to /login
